onary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Totes","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Spanish: habitational name from a place called Cotes in Valencia, probably a formation with the plural of Catalan <i>cot</i> ‘millstone’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Milon","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Czech: from a short form of various compound names formed with <i>mil</i> ‘grace, favour’, now also used in the English-speaking world. Sometimes, however, it may be chosen with reference to the northern Italian city (Italian <i>Milano</i>), the capital of Lombardy."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Milon de Lèves de Totes was born in 1125, in Lèves, Eure-et-Loir, Centre, France, his father, Goslein III de Lèves de Foucarmont, was 35 and his mother, Gertrude de Tôtes de Barentin, was 21. He married Mabile de Tremblay in 1154, in Tremblay, Ille-et-Vilaine, Brittany, France. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died on 22 November 1201, at the age of 76."},"et":{"1125–22 de novembro de 1201":"1125–22. november 1201","1125–1201":"1125–1201","1134–1187":"1134–1187","1130–1158":"1130–1158","1165–1226":"1165–1226","1155–1215":"1155–1215","1090–1151":"1090–1151","1104–Female":"1104–Surnud","1090":"1090","22 de novembro d